'''''Championship Baseball''''' is a [[sports video game]] developed by [[Activision]]'s [[Scott Orr#Gamestar|Gamestar]] division in 1986.

==Gameplay==
''Championship Baseball'' is a baseball simulation with a [[Split screen (video games)|split-screen]] to give the player a [[First-person (video games)|first-person]] view for both pitching and playing defense.<ref name="Dragon132"/>

==Reception==
''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' stated that ''Championship Baseball'' was a worthy sequel to Gamestar's ''Star League Baseball''.<ref name="teverbaugh198703">{{cite magazine | title=Sports Scoreboard | magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] | issue=35 | date=March 1987 | url=http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_35.pdf | accessdate=17 April 2016 | last=Teverbaugh | first=Rick | pages=14}}</ref> In 1988, ''[[Dragon (magazine)|Dragon]]'' gave the game 3½ out of 5 stars.<ref name="Dragon132">{{cite journal | title=The Role of Computers | last1=Lesser | last2=Lesser | last3=Lesser | first1=Hartley | first2=Patricia | first3=Kirk | journal=Dragon | issue=132 | date=April 1988 | pages=80–85}}</ref>

